<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>
    Python is an OS independant language, it allows us to write programmes and scripts. It is an interpreted language, not compiled like C++, Fortran etc. It can be used on any computer and has a variety of packages (libraries) which can be easily used.
</p>
<p>
    Memory is not managed in Python, data structures can be easily managed.
</p>

<p>
    Python is the language and we now have to install the interpreter on the computer. Start by opening the shell and typing the following BASH command.
</p>
